{
  "stem": "21310.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was my favorite aunt, my mother's favorite sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And she-- and I couldn't because they'd just had an action, you know, which is like a selection.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there was a lot of shooting and whatnot.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I couldn't get in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I-- you know, I didn't know where she was because everything was in a-- in a uproar inside the--",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--that area, in that ghetto, in that area where the Jews were.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I knew I probably couldn't find her anyway, and probably lose my life there, too.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I didn't-- I didn't go in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I-- I still feel very guilty about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Later on, my mother-- when I came back, my mother tried.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she couldn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She came too late.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she met-- she had some-- also some horrendous experiences on-- on the way.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "A German threw her down some steps and she ran after the train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The train was moving already.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she jumped on the bumper, the end, you know, the connection between cars, or that was the last one.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She jump and there was a Polish railroad man who pulled her up.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And she sat on this bumper at the end of the train with this Polish railroad man who was holding her.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- and she had also a big bag that she was carrying to take to her sister.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Anyway, she went-- she was bleeding because she had fallen down the steps when this German kicked them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so she-- she said, in her memoirs, she said she was only praying-- she was sure that she's going to die and fall off.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But this train was going through Otwock, where she knew I was and my father was.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
